HEADWORD: Ornithology
<hw>Or`ni*thol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Ornitho-</ets> + <ets>-logy</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>ornithologie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That branch of Zoology
which treats of the natural history of birds and their
classification.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A treatise or book on this science.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

